title: Google\Cloud\StorageTransfer\V1\AwsS3Data
name: AwsS3Data
description:
An AwsS3Data resource can be a data source, but not a data sink.

In an AwsS3Data resource, an object's name is the S3 object's key name.

Generated from protobuf message google.storagetransfer.v1.AwsS3Data

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.aws_access_key
params.description: Input only. AWS access key used to sign the API requests to the AWS S3 bucket. Permissions on the bucket must be granted to the access ID of the AWS access key. This field is required. For information on our data retention policy for user credentials, see User credentials.

params.name: data.path
params.description: Root path to transfer objects. Must be an empty string or full path name that ends with a '/'. This field is treated as an object prefix. As such, it should generally not begin with a '/'.

params.name: data.role_arn
params.description: Input only. Role arn to support temporary credentials via AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity. When role arn is provided, transfer service will fetch temporary credentials for the session using AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity call for the provided role using the [GoogleServiceAccount] for this project.
